    <descriptionSet>
      <description>Lamar Alexander won the 1978 Tennessee gubernatorial election over incumbent Ray Blanton by a wide margin. This button was part of Alexander’s re-election bid in 1982.  Referencing his trademark red and black plaid shirt and his walk across the state, this button was one of thousands distributed during the campaign. Alexander won re-election handily and served until January 1987.</description>
